---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Rhythmology — Heart Rhythm Disorders — Dr Delhasse" description="Diagnosis and treatment of heart rhythm disorders: bradycardia, tachycardia, atrial fibrillation. Dr Delhasse, FMH cardiologist." lang="en">

  <section class="hero-page">
    <div class="container">
      <h1><span class="text-primary">Rhythmology</span></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Your heart's electrical activity</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container detail-content">
      <img src="/images/svg/expertise/Rythmologie.svg" alt="Rhythmology" class="detail-icon" />

      <p>The heart normally beats 60 to 80 times per minute, approximately 100,000 times per day. During exercise, it can reach 140 to 200 beats per minute depending on age.</p>

      <p>Heart rhythm disorders manifest either as bradycardia (abnormally slow pulse) or tachycardia (abnormally fast pulse). Diagnosis relies on electrocardiograms or Holter recorders.</p>

      <p>Atrial arrhythmias are generally benign, while ventricular arrhythmias (tachycardias or fibrillation) can cause syncope and be potentially fatal without treatment.</p>

      <h2>Treatments</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Bradycardia:</strong> treated with pacemakers</li>
        <li><strong>Tachycardia:</strong> controlled by medications (beta-blockers, calcium channel blockers, amiodarone), catheter ablation, or implantable cardioverter-defibrillators (ICD)</li>
        <li><strong>Atrial fibrillation:</strong> the most common arrhythmia, caused by chaotic electrical circuits; can be stopped by electrical cardioversion or medications, with ablation if necessary</li>
      </ul>

      <p>The cardiologist helps patients understand their heart rhythm and proposes tailored management for a better quality of life.</p>

      <div class="detail-cta">
        <a href="/en/areas-of-expertise" class="btn btn--outline">&larr; All areas</a>
        <a href="/en/contact" class="btn btn--primary">Book an appointment</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .hero-page { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-navy) 0%, #1a3d6d 100%); padding: 6rem 0 4rem; color: var(--color-white); }
  .hero-page h1 { color: var(--color-white); font-size: 2.75rem; }
  .hero-sub { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75); font-size: 1.15rem; margin-top: 1rem; }
  .detail-content { max-width: 800px; }
  .detail-icon { width: 80px; height: 80px; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .detail-content p { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-gray); }
  .detail-content h2 { margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .detail-content ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .detail-content li { list-style: disc; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--color-gray); font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .detail-cta { display: flex; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .hero-page h1 { font-size: 2rem; } }
</style>
